So the presentations considered here are of a very special form.
If a group G is finite, then its multiplication table is finite. So we get a monadic
presentation for G by taking for each element (=£ 1) of the group a letter and for
T = {(ab,c)\a ■ b = c). It is easy to see that this is a finite reduced monadic
Church-Rosser presentation for G.
