In the next section we will omit the condition that each generator in the
presentation (2; T) under consideration has an inverse of length one. However, in
order to be able to prove the intended characterization, we have to restrict our
attention to Thue systems all the rules of which have left-hand sides of length two.
3. Two-monadic Thue systems. If a finite monadic Church-Rosser Thue system T
over 2 is reduced, and if each generator a g 2 has an inverse of length one, i.e., if
for each a G 2 there is some b g 2 such that ab <-» 1, then the left-hand side of
each rule of T is of length two, i.e., T c 22 X (2 U {1}). On the other hand, a finite
Church-Rosser Thue system T Q 22 X (2 U {1}) can be reduced without having an
inverse of length one for each of the generators from 2, although 2*/ «-»  is a
T
